# Service Implementation Guidelines

## Interface Location
Always define interfaces in `Infrastructures/Abstracts/`:
```csharp
// Abstracts/IMyService.cs
public interface IMyService
{
    Task<Result<string>> DoWorkAsync(string input);
}
```

## Implementation Location
Implement in `Infrastructures/Implements/`:
```csharp
// Implements/MyService.cs
public class MyService : IMyService
{
    public async Task<Result<string>> DoWorkAsync(string input)
    {
        // Implementation
    }
}
```

## Result Pattern
Service methods should return `Result<T>`:
```csharp
public async Task<Result<string>> GetDataAsync(string id)
{
    var data = await _context.Entities.FindAsync(id);
    
    return data is null 
        ? Result<string>.Failure("Not found") 
        : Result<string>.Success(data.Value);
}
```

## Caching Pattern
Implement cache-aside for read operations:
```csharp
// Check cache first
var cached = _cache.Get<string>(key);
if (cached != null) return Result<string>.Success(cached);

// Fall back to database
var data = await _context.Entities.FindAsync(key);
if (data != null) _cache.Add(key, data.Value);
```
